    "summary": "After a Master in Chemical Engineering I started my career in 1985 at the Philips Company in The Netherlands where I carried out projects on implementation of environmental friendly materials and clean technologies in the field of plastics, coatings and adhesives. A milestone was the introduction of water borne paintings in 1988.\nI worked in an international environment as Science Teacher in Papua New Guinea and set up projects in the field of sustainable development (Agenda 21) for UNESCO in India and surrounding countries.\nBack in The Netherlands I got an MBA in Environment Management and worked as Environment Consultant, till I joined the chemical industry in 2000 as EH&S leader. My special interests and experiences are in the field of Safety Awareness, Safety Training, Root Cause Investigation, Behavior Based Safety including ABC analysis and Influencer workshops. I was part of the CCvD - VCA (Safety Checklist Contractors) and contributed to the update of the VCA curriculum in 2008. \nIn November 2013 I joined the Sadara Chemical Company as EH&S Superintendent Supply Chain at its new industrial complex at Al Jubail in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.\nAfter my assignment in Saudi Arabia I returned to the Dow Chemical Company in the role of Occupational Hygiene Specialist for Dow Benelux BV.\nSince april 2023 I retired from Dow and continued as Independent Safety and Occupational Hygiene specialist, active in one of the Lexces TSB panels and in working groups of the NVVA and NVVK.",
